{"lemma":"صِبْغَةٌ","slug":"صِبْغَةٌ","root":"ص.ب.غ","root_slug":"ص-ب-غ","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ب-غ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صِبْغَة","root":"صبغ","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23717"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dye, colorant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tinge, a colour created by (or as if created by) dyeing"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the art of dyeing"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sˤib.ɣa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23717","headword_ar":"صِبْغَةٌ","root":"Sbg","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibogN","text_ar":"صِبْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence. ―         -b2-  It also means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diyn","text_ar":"دِين"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AA, O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mil~ap","text_ar":"مِلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religious law,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyEap","text_ar":"شَرِيعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything whereby one advances himself in the favour of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA:) [thus,] in the Kur [ii. 132], (O, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sibogapa A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"صِبْغَةَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the religion of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTorapa A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"فِطْرَةَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diyna A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"دِينَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) which is the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTorapa A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"فِطْرَةَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the religion of God, with an adaptation to which mankind are created;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because its effect appears in him who has it like the dye in the garment; (Bd, Jel;) or because it intermingles in the heart like the dye in the garment; (Bd;) and it is said to be from the Christians'"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabog","text_ar":"صَبْغ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabogap","text_ar":"صَبْغَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baptism"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of their children in a sort of water that they have; (S; [and the like is said in the O, and Ksh, & c.;])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sbgp","text_ar":"صبغة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being in this instance in the accus. case as an objective complement; (Msb;) for the meaning is “ follow ye the religion of God; ” (O, Msb;) or “ we will follow the religion of God: ” (O:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which God has prescribed"},{"kind":"text","text":"to Mohammad; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumcision:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sbgp","text_ar":"صبغة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in this instance an inf. n., (Ksh, Bd, Jel,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner of,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabog","text_ar":"صَبْغ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baptism"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Ksh,) relating to the baptism of the Christians, (Ksh, Bd,) a corroborative of the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=man~aA","text_ar":"ا=مَنَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in verse 130], as such put in the accusative case, (Ksh, Bd, Jel,) by reason of a verb understood, (Jel,) the meaning being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaganaA A@ll~`hu Sibogatahu","text_ar":"صَبَغَنَا ا@للّٰهُ صِبْغَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God hath baptized us with his baptism"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Ksh, Bd, Jel; *) [so that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sibogapa A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"صِبْغَةَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the baptism of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and may here be rendered We have received"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the baptism of God;;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the Muslims being hereby commanded to say to the Christians, “ Say ye, God hath baptized us ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaganaA","text_ar":"صَبَغَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") with the faith, with a baptism ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabogap","text_ar":"صَبْغَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") not like ours [i. e. not like our Christian baptism], and purified us with a purifying not like ours; ” or the Muslims being hereby commanded to say [of themselves], “ God hath baptized us ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaganaA","text_ar":"صَبَغَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") with the faith, as a baptism ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibogapF","text_ar":"صِبْغَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and we have not been baptized with your baptism ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo nuSobago Sibogatakumo","text_ar":"لَمْ نُصْبَغْ صِبْغَتَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). ” (Ksh.)"}],"source_refs":["AA","O","K","TA","Msb","S","Ksh","Bd","Jel"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}